text:
(1 & 2)
East River, shoreline, south from Gouveneur Lane to Coenties Slip, as viewed from pier 11, at the foot of Jones Lane. This is a set of two views.
February 1, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, as seen through the rigging of the Schooner R.R. Govin, at the foot of Pier No. 11, East River.
January 23, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

East River, showing pier 11, off South Street, at the foot of Jones Lane. Waste paper is being loaded on a barge for shipment to a Connecticut paper factory.
